Pre-manip avatar morphologies : statistical analyses

Experiment summary

This pre-manipulation aims to validate the perceived morphology of dynamic avatars. Participants viewed 12 animated avatars (randomized order) and rated each avatar on 6 adjective-based dimensions: athletic, average, overweight, obese, thin, skinny.

The mapping between ratings and avatars is reconstructed using: - VI03_01 VI03_12: the avatar identifier presented at each position (slot) - PM01_01 PM72_01: 72 ratings corresponding to 12 blocks of 6 adjectives (fixed order within each block)

Hypotheses

For each avatar, ratings will be higher on the adjective matching its intended morphology than on the non-matching adjectives (congruent > incongruent).

2. Data preparation

ratings_long %>%
  count(CASE) %>%
  summarise(min_n = min(n), max_n = max(n))
ratings_long <- ratings_long %>%
  mutate(
    CASE = as.factor(CASE),
    avatar = as.character(avatar),
    adjectif = as.factor(adjectif),
    note = as.numeric(note),
    DE03x01 = as.numeric(DE03x01)
  )

3. Exclusion

excluded_participants <- ratings_long %>%
  filter(DE10 %in% c(2, 3)) %>%
  distinct(CASE)

n_excluded <- nrow(excluded_participants)

ratings_clean <- ratings_long %>%
  filter(!(CASE %in% excluded_participants$CASE))

n_total <- ratings_long %>% distinct(CASE) %>% nrow()

n_excluded <- ratings_long %>%
  filter(DE10 %in% c(2, 3)) %>%
  distinct(CASE) %>%
  nrow()

n_included <- n_total - n_excluded

5. Manip-check

library(purrr)
library(dplyr)

adjectifs <- levels(ratings_clean$adjectif)

results_by_avatar <- ratings_clean %>%
  group_by(avatar) %>%
  group_modify(~ {
    
    data_av <- .x
    target <- unique(data_av$morpho_target)
    
    # Sparer congruent
    data_congruent <- data_av %>%
      filter(adjectif == target)
    
    # Comparer  chaque adjectif incongruent
    map_dfr(
      adjectifs[adjectifs != target],
      function(adj) {
        
        data_incongruent <- data_av %>%
          filter(adjectif == adj)
        
        test <- t.test(
          data_congruent$note,
          data_incongruent$note,
          paired = TRUE
        )
        
        tibble(
          morpho_target = target,
          compared_to = adj,
          t = as.numeric(test$statistic),
          p_value = test$p.value,
          mean_congruent = mean(data_congruent$note),
          mean_incongruent = mean(data_incongruent$note)
        )
      }
    )
  }) %>%
  ungroup()
results_by_avatar <- results_by_avatar %>%
  group_by(avatar) %>%
  mutate(
    p_adj = p.adjust(p_value, method = "holm"),
    significant = p_adj < .05
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

results_by_avatar
avatar_validation <- results_by_avatar %>%
  group_by(avatar) %>%
  summarise(
    all_contrasts_significant = all(significant),
    .groups = "drop"
  )

avatar_validation
library(ggplot2)

# Moyennes + SEM par avatar  adjectif
plot_data <- ratings_clean %>%
  group_by(avatar, adjectif, morpho_target) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_note = mean(note),
    sem = sd(note) / sqrt(n()),
    .groups = "drop"
  )
sig_labels <- results_by_avatar %>%
  mutate(
    label = ifelse(significant, "*", "ns")
  ) %>%
  left_join(
    plot_data,
    by = c("avatar", "compared_to" = "adjectif")
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    y_pos = mean_note + sem + 2  # ajustable si besoin
  )

6. Plots and export

library(purrr)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

# Fonction qui gnre le plot dun avatar
plot_one_avatar <- function(av_id){

  pd_av <- plot_data %>% filter(avatar == av_id)
  sig_av <- sig_labels %>% filter(avatar == av_id)

  ggplot(pd_av, aes(x = adjectif, y = mean_note)) +
    geom_col(
      aes(fill = adjectif == morpho_target),
      width = 0.7
    ) +
    geom_errorbar(
      aes(ymin = mean_note - sem, ymax = mean_note + sem),
      width = 0.2
    ) +
    geom_text(
      data = sig_av,
      aes(x = compared_to, y = y_pos, label = label),
      size = 4
    ) +
    scale_fill_manual(
      values = c("grey70", "steelblue"),
      labels = c("Incongruent", "Congruent"),
      name = ""
    ) +
    labs(
      title = paste("Avatar:", av_id),
      subtitle = "Congruent adjective vs each incongruent adjective (Holm-corrected)",
      x = "Adjective",
      y = "Mean rating"
    ) +
    theme_minimal(base_size = 12) +
    theme(
      axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
      legend.position = "top"
    )
}

# Afficher tous les avatars, un par un
avatar_list <- sort(unique(plot_data$avatar))
plots <- map(avatar_list, plot_one_avatar)

# Imprime dans le notebook
walk(plots, print)
